sql:
SELECT DISTINCT users.user_name, users.role
FROM users
INNER JOIN feedback ON users.user_id = feedback.user_id;

external_knowledge:
- "garden of recent discourse" metaphorically refers to the collection of articles;
- "blossoms have emerged" metaphorically refers to articles that have been published;
- "average length and emotional tone of the blooms" refer to the average word count and sentiment score of the articles;
- "count the total number of blossoms per topic" refers to the total articles per topic.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM articles 
WHERE sentiment_score >= (SELECT AVG(sentiment_score) FROM articles);

external_knowledge:
- Positive sentiment: refers to sentiment scores greater than 0.5 in this context;
- Opinion pieces: articles marked as 'is_opinion' = 1;
- Not ads: articles where 'is_ad' = 0.

sql:
SELECT article_id, COUNT(*) AS engagement_count
FROM article_engagement
GROUP BY article_id;
